description: Reference point, can be either depth (d), height (h) or elevation (e)
Low value to set values to NA if they are below this value
High value to set values to NA if they are above this value
Rate of change to set values to NA which change from the previous value by greater than this value
Set values to NA if there are consecutive values greater than this value
Interpolate values if there is a data gap less than this value
